<br>
It's been in my mind for some time to start a 'Paladin Only' guild on Firiona Vie for some time now; however rl circumstances earlier in the year forced me out of the game.<br>
<br>
Fortunately, I'll soon be making a return to Norrath; and thus the concept of the Paladin guild along with me.  In a nutshell, the basic concept is similar to that of Arthurian Legen - the fabled Knights of the Round Table (loosely).  A  strong roleplay guild facing off against the many evils of Norrath.<br>
<br>
I realize the need of raiding and such will require alliances with other guilds/individuals to fill out other classes (crowd control, healing, etc), but that should be easy enough to attain once we've established.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, I guess this is a &quot;Would anyone be interested thread&quot; more than anything.  Offhand, Im thinking no level reqs - as I'll be starting fresh here myself - as long as you show a desire to roleplay and be an asset to the community as a whole. <br>
<br>
I'm seeing the role of Paladin within the guild as that of Holy Warrior (much like the old D&amp;D concept), with all that come with that (from Chivalry down to not grouping with evils and the like - I've somewhat of a codex written up that can be &quot;set to stone at a later date).<br>
<br>
Right now, Im just looking to see if any unguilded (or unhappy) Paladins would be interested in helping set the foundation for this?<br>
<br>
Ansalon <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=loricleondegrance>LoricLeondegrance</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/10/03 8:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=658.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Paladin guild</span><hr size=1> Greetings Ansalon. An interesting idea you propose. While I do not currently consider myself an &quot;unhappy&quot; paladin, I am willing to help you make this dream become a reality. Feel free to contact me in game regarding this..<br>
